
* Uses Dave's new perfect 512 origin list

* allows configuring different sets of offsets for Kernel A and kernel B

* Improved meters (reported every 30 seconds, with sieve rate information and an
  estimate pf P[prime|sieved])

* Reduced chattiness (ony 6-chains are reported), improved formatting of output.

* Persistent Stats (found chains, chains per origin, running time, accepted/rejected work)
  saved to miningstats text file, with 30 second checkpointing intervals.
  
* Stats are also saved on CTRL-C or SIGTERM

